<br>
The question:  How the heck do you guys manage these crazy far-off vanishing points?  Is there something I'm missing?  Do I need a protractor and my Trig book?<br>
<br>
Sub-question:  How do I draw a perfect cube in two-point perspective?  Is the ratio of the visual widths of the two visible sides equal to the ratio of the respective vanishing point's distance to the corner of the cube or something like that?  I've looked around and nobody I've read says anything about that.<br>
<br>
Hmph. <p><b>Shpydir</b><br>
