<br>
Alucard showed this link a few days ago.  I thought it was appropriate.  It should help with the square thing.<br>
<br>
as for the vanishing points question, I'm not really sure myself.  One option might be to try drawing a thumbnail version of what you want to draw first, and then redrawing it bigger since most of the angles would remain the same.  I don't know if anyone actually uses that method, but it's a thought.  I'm still trying to figure out a lot of this stuff too.  <br>
<br>
I know there are some mathematical rules you could follow, but I actually have yet to find a good book that explains that subject.  Anyone have a recommendation besides &quot;Perspective for Comic Book Artists?&quot;<br>
<br>
[edit]<br>
Also, just as an additional question to add on to here since I was actually going to write up a big perspective related post too, I was wondering what formal methods many of you are actually using.  <br>
<br>
Some of the ones I've seen seem like they can become pretty tedious to use to get accurate representations, which I assume is necessary in some cases, but are you actually using them all the time, or do you just rely on your eyes to tell you if something looks right?  I guess what I want to know is which methods or shortcuts do you use the most?<br>
